# Digital Image Processing

# Feature Detection and Description

According to the given text, a feature is defined as a specific pattern or unique element in an image that can be easily tracked and compared across different images. Features are crucial for tasks like assembling images (similar to a jigsaw puzzle) or creating 3D models from multiple images. The text emphasizes that good features, such as corners, are easily identifiable because they look different regardless of their position in the image, making them effective for comparison and alignment. Overall, features are the distinctive characteristics in images that facilitate recognition and matching processes.
